npc1: Wait. Before you reach that door — look at it. It is locked.
npc1: Every place like this is easy to walk into. Walking out is the part they never advertise.
npc1: Most people think the way out is one more win. One big payout to cover everything they lost. That key never drops.
npc1: I searched for it for two years. I borrowed money. I chased losses. I lied to people who loved me. The door stayed shut.
npc1: You know what finally opened it? Not luck. Not money. Admitting I needed help — and letting someone hand me the key.
npc1: So I am handing it to you. Take it. This is what getting out actually looks like.
npc1: One more thing, because you will need it out there.
npc1: You are going to slip. Everyone slips. The danger is not the first wrong step.
npc1: The danger is what comes after — chasing it. One loss, so you risk more to win it back. Then more. That is the fall.
npc1: So learn to catch yourself in mid-air. The moment you feel yourself dropping, jump again. Pull yourself back up.
npc1: Call it a second chance. You always have one, as long as you choose to use it.
npc1: Now go. The door will open for you.
